WEBVTT

00:00.007 --> 00:02.340
<i>- Previously on "The Family"... </i>
- What does he look like?

00:02.487 --> 00:04.246
H-He has holes in his face.

00:04.733 --> 00:07.386
Anyone who has ever worked
at this refinery

00:07.440 --> 00:09.147
could've known how
to get into that tunnel.

00:09.234 --> 00:10.900
[Gasps] Oh! Oh, God.

00:11.002 --> 00:12.268
You are early.

00:12.370 --> 00:13.836
I couldn't wait to see my baby.

00:13.939 --> 00:16.105
- Aww.
- Both my babies.

00:16.207 --> 00:20.543
I am announcing
my candidacy for governor.

00:20.645 --> 00:23.146
Could I have a minute alone?
Just a minute?

00:23.248 --> 00:28.017
Bridey: The older brother's not
totally sure Adam is Adam.

00:28.119 --> 00:29.719
How the hell did you get that?

00:29.821 --> 00:32.255
Julia: Would you consider your
neighbor Hank Asher a monster?

00:32.357 --> 00:33.489
Yeah, absolutely. Yes, yes, I would.

00:33.591 --> 00:35.058
If he had been chipped

00:35.160 --> 00:37.126
after being convicted
of his first sex offense,

00:37.228 --> 00:37.898
we could've cleared him.

00:38.033 --> 00:39.729
- When did it start?
- What?

00:39.831 --> 00:41.631
You sleeping with the dad.

00:41.733 --> 00:42.542
Few months after.

00:42.567 --> 00:44.358
Just wondering if it ever
clouded your vision.

00:44.436 --> 00:46.035
I'm sorry for what happened to you.

00:46.137 --> 00:47.203
You happened to me.

00:47.305 --> 00:49.138
Your family happened to me.

00:49.271 --> 00:50.473
Why did you confess?

00:50.575 --> 00:51.908
They had stuff on me.

00:52.010 --> 00:53.876
We stopped looking because
you said you killed him.

00:53.945 --> 00:56.179
I didn't lock the boy in a basement.

00:56.281 --> 00:58.815
No. You just made sure
that he stayed there.

01:01.786 --> 01:05.054
♪

01:05.123 --> 01:08.725
Claire: <i>Most of us never find
out what we're really made of.</i>

01:11.463 --> 01:14.163
<i>If we could lift a car off someone... </i>

01:18.069 --> 01:19.320
<i>... save a life... </i>

01:23.855 --> 01:24.878
<i>... take one.</i>

01:30.315 --> 01:33.416
♪ Silent night ♪

01:33.518 --> 01:36.252
<i>If they cut you open,
what would they find... </i>

01:36.354 --> 01:39.317
- ♪ Holy night ♪ <i>
- ... feathers or steel?</i>

01:40.692 --> 01:43.113
- ♪ Shepherds quake ♪ <i>
- Answer me that</i>

01:43.138 --> 01:45.218
... I'll tell you if you're a mother.

01:45.296 --> 01:46.963
Hank: You're not on my list.

01:47.065 --> 01:49.832
- ♪ At the sight ♪
- Excuse me?

01:50.869 --> 01:53.136
I get to choose who visits me.

01:53.238 --> 01:57.173
♪ Christ the Savior is born ♪

01:57.275 --> 01:58.845
It's the little things.

02:00.101 --> 02:02.278
I was recently elected mayor.

02:02.380 --> 02:05.214
- ♪ Christ the Savior is born ♪
- I read about that.

02:05.316 --> 02:07.850
I don't have to be on a list.

02:08.853 --> 02:10.286
That would explain it.

02:10.388 --> 02:11.621
Where's my son?

02:13.958 --> 02:15.691
What did you do with his body?

02:17.295 --> 02:19.729
I can't help you with that.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.441
I'm not asking for an apology.

02:25.770 --> 02:29.138
I don't want to see you cry or beg.

02:29.240 --> 02:33.676
I just want to have
a funeral for my child

02:33.778 --> 02:35.211
with a body in the casket.

02:35.313 --> 02:37.380
That's all I need from you.
Do you understand me?

02:40.418 --> 02:42.251
[Exhales shakily]

02:42.353 --> 02:44.954
So what did you do with him
after you murdered him?

02:45.056 --> 02:47.177
I can't help you with that.

02:51.529 --> 02:52.762
We're done here.

02:57.635 --> 03:00.103
[Bell rings]

03:03.079 --> 03:05.079
_

03:05.510 --> 03:07.543
[Glass shatters]

03:09.114 --> 03:10.613
[Dog barking in distance]

03:12.000 --> 03:18.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:29.601 --> 03:33.202
♪

03:53.543 --> 03:55.543
_

04:03.368 --> 04:11.697
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

04:14.279 --> 04:16.178
Cover of "The Trib," "USA Today,"

04:16.281 --> 04:17.613
"The Herald," "The Post,"

04:17.714 --> 04:21.083
"New York Times"...
page three over the fold...

04:21.185 --> 04:23.619
- Well, no one reads that one.
- I do.

04:23.721 --> 04:25.621
You'll get the endorsement,
Simpson drops out,

04:25.723 --> 04:27.023
then it's just you against Lang.

04:27.125 --> 04:28.958
An incumbent governor
with very deep pockets.

04:29.060 --> 04:31.160
Whose track record
we can play like a dart board.

04:31.262 --> 04:34.197
Please. You're the next governor
of Maine, mother.

04:34.299 --> 04:35.198
It's...

04:35.300 --> 04:37.500
Danny: Good morning.

04:38.937 --> 04:40.036
Morning.

04:40.138 --> 04:42.329
- Morning.
- Morning.

04:42.431 --> 04:44.636
[Muffled] You want coffee
or anything before you go?

04:44.738 --> 04:46.042
Um...

04:46.177 --> 04:47.476
Danny...

04:49.581 --> 04:52.381
This is Bridey. From high school.

04:54.419 --> 04:55.785
She's not a hooker.

04:55.887 --> 04:57.486
Oh. [Chuckles]

04:57.622 --> 04:59.555
Why don't you sit, honey?

04:59.657 --> 05:00.990
Who wants waffles?

05:01.059 --> 05:02.658
If it's not too much trouble...

05:04.229 --> 05:05.127
Seriously?

05:05.230 --> 05:07.129
Go see if Adam's hungry, will you?

05:07.232 --> 05:09.899
Yeah. Go see if Adam's hungry.

05:15.406 --> 05:17.106
I'm sorry.

05:19.877 --> 05:21.944
It's not your fault.

05:22.046 --> 05:23.980
Yes, it is.

05:26.150 --> 05:28.384
It'll come off.

05:38.563 --> 05:41.030
You don't have to do that.

05:44.569 --> 05:47.270
You shouldn't be here.

05:49.307 --> 05:51.307
It's not coming off.

05:51.442 --> 05:53.542
Claire: Adam!

05:58.016 --> 05:59.316
Please.

06:00.618 --> 06:01.948
Go.

06:07.992 --> 06:10.026
[Telephone ringing]

06:14.299 --> 06:15.831
Hey.

06:15.933 --> 06:18.768
You look like you ate one of
those vegan muffins Teresa made.

06:18.870 --> 06:20.002
Very upsetting.

06:20.104 --> 06:21.110
An 8-year-old boy was snatched

06:21.135 --> 06:23.472
from Rosemont Park an hour ago.

06:23.574 --> 06:26.409
His mother assaulted
and knocked unconscious.

06:26.511 --> 06:27.710
Looks just like Adam.

06:27.812 --> 06:28.978
M.O.'s the same, too...

06:29.080 --> 06:31.547
broad daylight in a public park.

06:34.085 --> 06:35.117
[Dog barking in distance]

06:35.219 --> 06:36.752
[Door opens]

06:36.854 --> 06:39.021
Jane: Doug, where have you been?

06:39.123 --> 06:41.290
- [Door closes]
- I sent you like 20 texts this morning.

06:41.392 --> 06:43.426
- What were you...
- Everything looks terrific, girls.

06:43.494 --> 06:44.493
Doug?!

06:44.595 --> 06:46.962
♪

06:52.637 --> 06:54.303
Think it's a copycat?

06:54.405 --> 06:56.872
Well, some guy's watching
the news, decides to take a kid

06:56.941 --> 06:59.141
the exact same way
Adam Warren was taken?

06:59.243 --> 07:00.943
Maybe.

07:38.583 --> 07:40.649
What if it's not a copycat?

07:40.752 --> 07:42.294
He lost Adam...

07:43.354 --> 07:45.234
so he found himself a new one.

07:57.911 --> 07:59.464
♪ The snow is snowing,
candlelight is glowing ♪

07:59.489 --> 08:01.461
What kind of sick, depraved monster...

08:01.544 --> 08:03.891
- ♪ It is Christmas time at last ♪
- Are we really doing this right now?

08:04.044 --> 08:05.443
It wasn't enough
for him to kill a child?

08:05.545 --> 08:06.414
That didn't get his rocks off?

08:06.517 --> 08:07.391
Tonight?

08:08.004 --> 08:09.841
- ♪ Christmastime ♪
- I want to have a funeral for my son.

08:09.944 --> 08:11.517
Well, then, have one.
Why can't we just...

08:11.653 --> 08:13.753
I'm not burying an empty coffin, John!

08:13.855 --> 08:16.956
♪ Children singing in the snow ♪

08:17.058 --> 08:18.724
Got to move on.

08:18.860 --> 08:21.014
- ♪ It is Christmas time at last ♪
- Chapter three of your book?

08:21.116 --> 08:22.641
It's been almost two years.

08:22.743 --> 08:24.730
Sorry if I'm not grieving
gracefully enough for you.

08:24.799 --> 08:28.901
♪ 12:00, Christmas Eve, Santa is on... ♪

08:29.003 --> 08:31.470
- [Indistinct shouting]
- Woman: Mayor Warren, can you comment?

08:31.572 --> 08:33.339
Is it true the police
suspect the same man

08:33.441 --> 08:34.373
who took Adam may also be...

08:34.475 --> 08:35.508
That's unconfirmed.

08:35.610 --> 08:37.143
You're proposing a law
to chip sex offenders.

08:37.245 --> 08:38.410
Would that have helped at all
in this case?

08:38.513 --> 08:40.246
There's a child missing.
We're not gonna politicize that.

08:40.347 --> 08:42.248
Scotty: We got job growth
locked down, governor,

08:42.350 --> 08:44.316
but we need to shore up
our position on crime.

08:44.419 --> 08:45.985
A few juicy sound bites
can go a long way.

08:46.087 --> 08:47.720
Yeah, well, I'm not gonna do that today.

08:47.822 --> 08:49.321
Claire Warren has made crime an issue.

08:49.424 --> 08:51.090
- I'm not gonna talk about it.
- But <i> she's</i> talking about it.

08:51.192 --> 08:52.525
So, let her talk about it.

08:52.627 --> 08:55.194
Mayor Warren, have you spoken
to the Daniels family yet?

08:55.296 --> 08:57.863
Obviously, I can imagine
what they're going through.

08:57.965 --> 09:00.399
I want to point out
that the police have issued

09:00.501 --> 09:02.835
an amber alert for a white van

09:02.937 --> 09:07.973
with the license plate
beginning with "3JKE."

09:08.076 --> 09:09.442
She's a one-trick pony, Scotty...

09:09.544 --> 09:11.177
a lightweight, small-town mayor

09:11.279 --> 09:12.812
running a one-issue campaign.

09:12.914 --> 09:14.146
Believe me... people are gonna get tired

09:14.248 --> 09:15.981
of sex offenders and microchips.

09:16.084 --> 09:17.650
So, let her jump through
her pretty hoops

09:17.719 --> 09:18.684
and her pretty ring.

09:18.786 --> 09:20.052
And when the kids are done clapping

09:20.154 --> 09:21.554
for the pretty, pretty pony,

09:21.656 --> 09:23.756
we will get down to the real issues.

09:23.858 --> 09:25.224
It's enough already!

09:25.326 --> 09:27.560
No parent should have to
go through this nightmare.

09:27.628 --> 09:29.962
And if the man who took Brian
is watching right now,

09:30.064 --> 09:31.630
I want you to listen to me
very carefully.

09:31.699 --> 09:33.766
You are on borrowed time.

09:33.868 --> 09:36.035
We may not know your name
or where you live,

09:36.137 --> 09:37.603
but we know who you are.

09:37.705 --> 09:39.705
And we will find you.

09:44.212 --> 09:46.112
Isn't this a press conference?

09:46.214 --> 09:47.646
Yes, sir.

09:47.749 --> 09:49.482
So, where's the damn press?

09:50.318 --> 09:53.085
[Indistinct shouting]

09:53.187 --> 09:55.011
<i>Sources say they have
reason to believe... </i>

09:55.036 --> 09:56.259
She made me a latte this morning...

09:56.304 --> 09:57.679
<i>- ... the kidnapping may be connected... </i>
- ... with almond milk.

09:57.747 --> 09:58.891
<i>... to the Adam Warren case.</i>

09:58.993 --> 10:01.827
What does your bang buddy think?

10:01.929 --> 10:04.296
He's suspicious, but
he's too close to it to tell.

10:04.398 --> 10:05.898
So, he lets the fox into the henhouse

10:06.033 --> 10:07.700
to figure it out for him.

10:07.802 --> 10:08.901
That's ballsy.

10:09.003 --> 10:12.838
Somebody get me an almond-milk latte.

10:12.940 --> 10:14.974
- Gus!
- What?

10:15.076 --> 10:17.597
- It's his family.
- So?

10:17.699 --> 10:19.345
So, I promised him
I would give him a heads up

10:19.447 --> 10:20.946
before we ran with anything.

10:21.048 --> 10:22.248
Well, I didn't.

10:22.350 --> 10:25.718
♪

10:38.800 --> 10:40.866
[Knock on door]

10:49.210 --> 10:51.143
You try a pressure wash?

10:51.245 --> 10:53.379
- What?
- On your garage.

10:53.481 --> 10:55.180
Probably take some paint off,

10:55.282 --> 10:56.835
but better than what's on it now.

10:57.318 --> 10:59.364
Hank Asher, right?

11:01.428 --> 11:03.364
You've been served
with a restraining order.

11:03.718 --> 11:06.058
You're not to come in contact
with or disturb the peace

11:06.127 --> 11:09.261
of John and Claire Warren
or anyone in their family,

11:09.330 --> 11:11.831
including their son Adam.

11:15.909 --> 11:17.340
He came over <i> here.</i>

11:17.442 --> 11:20.372
100 yards, okay?

11:22.510 --> 11:24.944
They live across the street.

11:28.549 --> 11:31.350
Then don't go past that tree.

11:38.392 --> 11:41.060
So, we found four surveillance
cameras near the park.

11:41.162 --> 11:42.928
My team's already
combing through the footage.

11:42.997 --> 11:44.663
Anything on the license plate?

11:44.765 --> 11:46.866
Stolen off an Accord
in New Haven three days ago.

11:46.968 --> 11:48.601
That's helpful.

11:48.703 --> 11:51.070
"What about the tip line?" he asked,

11:51.172 --> 11:52.304
already knowing the answer.

11:52.406 --> 11:54.373
Flooded, thanks to Warren's
press conference.

11:54.475 --> 11:57.276
Anything other than the usual
shut-ins and crackpots?

11:57.378 --> 11:58.911
Even if someone calls with something,

11:59.013 --> 12:00.713
i-it'll take forever
to find them in the haystack.

12:00.815 --> 12:02.047
We don't have forever.

12:02.116 --> 12:03.182
No, we do not.

12:03.284 --> 12:05.951
[Cellphone chimes]

12:06.020 --> 12:09.588
But we have... this.

12:20.835 --> 12:22.401
What do you think, Adam?

12:22.503 --> 12:26.338
Take your time, honey. There's no rush.

12:32.179 --> 12:33.572
- Oh, God, Adam.
- Get him some water.

12:33.674 --> 12:34.246
Adam!

12:34.348 --> 12:35.915
- I gotcha. I gotcha.
- God!

12:36.951 --> 12:38.717
Okay. Come here.

12:40.688 --> 12:42.288
Is that him?

12:42.390 --> 12:44.924
Is... Is that h... Is that him?
Is that the man that took you?

12:45.059 --> 12:46.191
Claire: For God's sakes,
give him a minute.

12:46.294 --> 12:47.359
That's him, isn't it?

12:47.461 --> 12:50.095
♪

13:02.624 --> 13:03.823
You've been assistant warden

13:03.958 --> 13:06.513
at Sinclair State Prison
for 12 years now.

13:06.594 --> 13:08.160
[Chuckles] Got the scars to prove it.

13:08.262 --> 13:11.471
Well, compared to herding inmates,

13:12.119 --> 13:14.411
heading up my security detail

13:14.685 --> 13:17.505
should be a lazy Sunday afternoon.

13:18.651 --> 13:20.340
Welcome to the team. Thank you.

13:21.395 --> 13:23.162
Give us a minute, Diane?

13:30.926 --> 13:33.026
Were you able to... find out?

13:33.128 --> 13:34.628
Uh, I wasn't.

13:34.730 --> 13:36.897
[Sighs] But you had people speak to him?

13:36.999 --> 13:38.765
He won't say a word.

13:38.867 --> 13:40.567
[Sighs]

13:43.432 --> 13:45.031
Is there anything else I can do?

13:49.545 --> 13:52.079
[Bell rings]

13:52.181 --> 13:55.449
♪

14:10.933 --> 14:12.666
[Grunts]

14:18.240 --> 14:21.274
[Breathing heavily]

14:34.123 --> 14:36.292
["Granite Feast" plays]

14:36.333 --> 14:38.333
_

14:55.711 --> 14:59.379
♪ I went to the village
and I knock on the door ♪

14:59.481 --> 15:01.915
♪ To find what I was looking for ♪

15:02.017 --> 15:05.252
♪ My eyes weren't blind,
but I could not see ♪

15:05.354 --> 15:07.921
♪ Why they would not talk to me ♪

15:08.023 --> 15:12.859
♪ And the court clown
danced upon the table ♪

15:12.928 --> 15:15.629
♪ Threw the porcelain to the ground ♪

15:15.698 --> 15:17.625
What can I do for you, Mr. Asher?

15:19.297 --> 15:23.737
I want to sue the Warrens for
slander and... and defamation.

15:24.143 --> 15:26.640
- The mayor's family.
- That's right.

15:27.176 --> 15:28.308
[Sighs]

15:28.410 --> 15:29.810
Can I ask how...

15:29.912 --> 15:31.411
She and her husband contributed

15:31.513 --> 15:33.847
to my being wrongfully incarcerated.

15:33.982 --> 15:35.549
You got a big payout from that.

15:37.319 --> 15:39.799
She called me a monster
on national television.

15:40.219 --> 15:41.477
Not exactly grounds for...

15:41.579 --> 15:43.154
[Muffled] There are other things, too.

15:44.667 --> 15:45.859
Mr. Asher.

15:45.961 --> 15:47.101
Hank.

15:47.629 --> 15:49.396
Yeah.

15:49.498 --> 15:52.466
You're a convicted sex offender.
She's a mother.

15:52.568 --> 15:54.225
Who made my life a living hell.

15:54.328 --> 15:55.669
Who lost her son.

15:55.771 --> 15:58.972
♪ And the court clown
danced upon the table ♪

15:59.074 --> 16:03.009
My advice...
use that money they gave you

16:03.112 --> 16:06.086
and go buy yourself an island.

16:06.188 --> 16:08.794
- I don't want an island.
- What do you want?

16:09.418 --> 16:10.729
Justice.

16:11.453 --> 16:14.020
♪ Said my head spinning all around ♪

16:14.123 --> 16:15.422
Good luck.

16:27.002 --> 16:29.236
What if I was wrong? What if
it's been him this whole time?

16:29.338 --> 16:30.804
- Okay, calm down.
- No, no, no, no, no.

16:30.906 --> 16:31.720
You didn't see him today, all right?

16:31.829 --> 16:34.047
When they showed him of the guy,
he... he flipped out.

16:34.109 --> 16:35.273
He almost passed out.
You can't fake that.

16:35.375 --> 16:36.943
Look, you didn't do anything wrong.

16:37.045 --> 16:38.311
You were just looking for the truth.

16:38.413 --> 16:40.147
Yeah, yeah, so I called a reporter.

16:40.249 --> 16:43.583
Here. Let's go somewhere
and get a drink...

16:43.652 --> 16:46.086
No, Bridey. I'm not drinking.

16:46.188 --> 16:48.188
No, I know. I'm sorry.

16:48.290 --> 16:49.222
Ju... Ju...

16:50.859 --> 16:52.425
You didn't tell anyone, did you?

16:52.528 --> 16:54.461
Of course not.

16:54.563 --> 16:55.729
[Elevator bell dings]

16:57.566 --> 16:59.299
I'm your friend.

16:59.401 --> 17:00.734
Yeah.

17:09.377 --> 17:12.311
You can't disappear today, okay?
It's a couples shower.

17:12.414 --> 17:13.770
I'll be here. I will.

17:13.872 --> 17:16.016
If I have to play
those stupid games alone.

17:16.117 --> 17:17.416
- [Chuckles]
- [Scoffs]

17:17.519 --> 17:18.752
Hey, where are you going?

17:18.854 --> 17:20.820
You left the sherbet in the deep freeze.

17:20.923 --> 17:22.155
No.

17:22.257 --> 17:24.023
What do you mean no?

17:24.126 --> 17:26.792
I had to put down rat traps.
There's loose floorboards.

17:26.895 --> 17:28.428
It isn't safe.

17:29.832 --> 17:31.298
[Laughs]

17:31.400 --> 17:32.833
- I have to go out again. Real fast.
- What?!

17:32.935 --> 17:35.039
I'll be back in time.
I'll do everything.

17:35.141 --> 17:36.636
Only you have to promise me...

17:36.738 --> 17:38.104
What?

17:38.207 --> 17:39.806
... you won't go in there.

17:39.908 --> 17:42.108
[Scoffs]

17:42.177 --> 17:43.944
Okay.

17:44.613 --> 17:46.179
That's my girl.

17:46.281 --> 17:49.182
[Chuckles]

17:49.251 --> 17:50.750
Got a lead on the tip line.

17:50.853 --> 17:52.219
The perp has blonde to black hair,

17:52.321 --> 17:53.687
is of short to tall build,

17:53.789 --> 17:56.156
and either has a beard
or no beard at all?

17:56.258 --> 17:57.691
Man says a white van
with the right plates

17:57.759 --> 17:58.859
just stopped for gas at his station,

17:58.961 --> 18:01.294
left 15 minutes ago,
headed north on 100.

18:01.363 --> 18:03.830
♪

18:17.846 --> 18:20.046
[Sighs]

18:21.316 --> 18:23.149
- Oh, my God.
- Claire: What?

18:23.252 --> 18:25.285
They... They... They caught him.
CNN says he's in custody.

18:25.387 --> 18:26.686
What?!

18:28.891 --> 18:30.323
Uh, no.

18:30.425 --> 18:32.125
W-Wait. No. They made a mistake.

18:32.227 --> 18:34.961
He, uh... They were wrong.
They're taking it back.

18:41.036 --> 18:43.303
Okay, come on, Ad.

18:43.405 --> 18:44.537
Where are you taking him?

18:44.640 --> 18:45.906
He needs to get some air.

18:46.041 --> 18:47.974
- John.
- There's none in here.

18:55.050 --> 18:57.584
[ <i> "Lazy Bones" plays</i> ]

19:01.089 --> 19:03.890
I've never seen you eat anything
not in bar form.

19:03.992 --> 19:05.659
- ♪<i> Na, na-na-na-na</i> ♪
- Sometimes you got to get the job done.

19:05.761 --> 19:07.072
Bars get the job done.

19:07.174 --> 19:08.069
♪<i> Early in the morning</i> ♪

19:08.094 --> 19:10.054
Now we know
what your headstone's gonna say.

19:10.132 --> 19:11.398
You sure you can look for this van

19:11.500 --> 19:13.266
and be superior at the same time?

19:13.368 --> 19:14.801
♪<i> Think you can leave</i> ♪

19:14.903 --> 19:16.036
♪<i> Only wake up to you</i> ♪

19:16.138 --> 19:18.972
My husband was an air-traffic
controller at Logan.

19:19.074 --> 19:20.710
That must have sucked.

19:20.805 --> 19:22.523
- ♪ <i>The mountains, while you're sleeping</i> ♪
- Yeah, so bad, he got an ulcer.

19:22.598 --> 19:23.199
♪<i> While you're sleeping,
While you're sleeping</i> ♪

19:23.224 --> 19:24.935
He quit, and we bought
five acres and some bees.

19:25.013 --> 19:26.096
Say what?

19:26.121 --> 19:27.823
- ♪<i> Saturday night is here</i> ♪
- We make honey now,

19:27.848 --> 19:30.307
and Jonah's ulcer is cured.

19:30.385 --> 19:32.085
- ♪<i> Make me some coffee</i> ♪
- It's the enzymes.

19:32.187 --> 19:34.688
- ♪<i> Sunday night you say</i> ♪
- I'm not saying you need to keep bees,

19:34.790 --> 19:36.792
but you got to bring a little joy
into this job or you're never...

19:36.894 --> 19:37.991
Hold on!

19:38.093 --> 19:40.493
[Tires squealing]

19:42.297 --> 19:43.563
[Tires screech]

19:43.665 --> 19:44.731
What the hell?

19:44.833 --> 19:46.599
Look.

19:53.041 --> 19:55.842
Doug: <i>Hi, it's Doug. Leave me a
message when you hear the beep.</i>

19:55.944 --> 19:57.243
[ <i>Beep</i> ]

19:57.346 --> 19:59.646
You promised you'd be back.
I can't keep making excuses.

19:59.748 --> 20:01.414
Where are you?

20:01.516 --> 20:02.549
[Cellphone beeps]

20:02.684 --> 20:05.318
♪

20:24.139 --> 20:26.906
Okay, so, choke up on the bat a little.

20:27.009 --> 20:28.508
Yeah.

20:28.610 --> 20:29.709
Good.

20:29.811 --> 20:31.244
Elbow up.

20:38.420 --> 20:40.153
Yeah, good.

20:58.774 --> 21:00.807
[Toilet flushes]

21:12.521 --> 21:14.554
[Water running]

21:17.692 --> 21:20.860
♪

21:32.174 --> 21:34.674
[Doorknob rattles]

21:38.313 --> 21:40.180
Sorry I'm late, everyone.

21:40.282 --> 21:43.216
♪

