21:59.484 --> 22:04.187
♪ All I want for Christmas ♪

22:04.289 --> 22:07.323
♪ Is for you to be near ♪

22:07.392 --> 22:10.293
♪ Be near ♪

22:10.395 --> 22:12.592
♪ Be near ♪

22:12.694 --> 22:19.769
♪ To warm me up with kisses and cheer ♪

22:19.871 --> 22:22.805
♪ And cheer ♪

22:22.908 --> 22:24.579
- ♪ And cheer ♪
- You first, Mom.

22:24.681 --> 22:27.911
- ♪ I think I may have missed it ♪
- From... Daddy.

22:28.013 --> 22:29.812
[Chuckles]

22:29.915 --> 22:35.585
♪ Maybe even wished it ♪

22:35.687 --> 22:44.394
♪ My only Christmas wish is
for you to be near ♪

22:44.496 --> 22:46.663
- ♪ Be near ♪
- [Chuckles]

22:46.765 --> 22:48.598
- ♪ Be near ♪
- [Chuckles]

22:48.700 --> 22:51.768
♪ Fa-la-la, fa-la-la ♪

22:51.870 --> 22:54.704
♪ Fa-la-la, aha ♪

22:54.806 --> 22:57.874
♪ Fa-la-la, fa-la-la ♪

22:57.976 --> 23:00.710
- ♪ Fa-la-la, ahahh ♪
- Excuse me.

23:07.052 --> 23:12.322
♪ All I want for Christmas ♪

23:12.424 --> 23:15.024
♪ This year ♪

23:15.126 --> 23:17.427
♪ This year ♪

23:17.495 --> 23:19.028
♪ This year ♪

23:19.130 --> 23:25.268
♪ Still warm you up with kisses ♪

23:25.337 --> 23:27.337
♪ And cheer ♪

23:27.439 --> 23:30.406
♪ And cheer ♪

23:30.508 --> 23:31.441
♪ And cheer ♪

23:31.543 --> 23:37.246
♪ I think I have missed it ♪

23:39.030 --> 23:40.663
[Door opens]

23:42.110 --> 23:43.833
- [Door closes]
- _

23:43.935 --> 23:45.635
[Grunts] It's not him.

23:45.704 --> 23:47.337
- Claire: What?
- John: How do you know?

23:47.439 --> 23:49.707
He was in prison when Adam was taken,

23:49.973 --> 23:51.873
uh, for rape and attempted murder.

23:52.067 --> 23:54.758
The kid's his ex-girlfriend's.

23:54.860 --> 23:58.274
It smells like
some kind of sick revenge thing.

24:00.187 --> 24:01.413
Where's Nina?

24:02.626 --> 24:03.920
There were shots fired.

24:04.023 --> 24:05.040
- Is she hurt?
- Dad.

24:05.142 --> 24:06.100
Is she hurt?

24:06.994 --> 24:07.950
No.

24:08.053 --> 24:09.719
She's fine.

24:09.821 --> 24:12.488
But that's all I can tell you right now.

24:33.078 --> 24:34.911
[Sighs]

24:35.013 --> 24:36.179
Riker: Let's review.

24:37.449 --> 24:39.120
When you entered the room,

24:39.189 --> 24:41.280
did you immediately identify yourself

24:41.382 --> 24:42.385
as a police officer?

24:42.775 --> 24:44.120
Yes, I did.

24:47.322 --> 24:49.020
When did you see Brian Daniels?

24:49.122 --> 24:50.693
As soon as I got inside.

24:51.261 --> 24:53.510
And you believed him
to be in immediate danger

24:53.612 --> 24:54.630
from Mr. Lipton?

24:55.241 --> 24:56.528
I did.

24:57.230 --> 24:58.510
He was.

24:58.898 --> 25:00.820
Mr. Lipton had a gun.

25:02.434 --> 25:04.040
Which he pointed at you.

25:04.495 --> 25:05.527
Yes.

25:07.057 --> 25:08.678
And did you tell him to drop the gun?

25:11.282 --> 25:12.482
Yes.

25:13.092 --> 25:14.319
And what was his response?

25:15.579 --> 25:16.719
He did not.

25:17.445 --> 25:18.909
And Agent Clements...

25:19.012 --> 25:21.090
he can confirm your version of events?

25:30.125 --> 25:32.455
He's all right. Was the guy armed?

25:32.557 --> 25:33.669
No.

25:38.444 --> 25:39.701
What do you want to do here?

25:42.359 --> 25:44.192
Got to do it now.

25:44.349 --> 25:46.849
[Sirens wailing in distance]

25:47.252 --> 25:50.153
♪

26:03.225 --> 26:05.468
Agent Clements will confirm, yes.

26:11.476 --> 26:13.342
Hey.

26:20.620 --> 26:22.227
How does it work?

26:23.500 --> 26:26.706
I'm not gonna let anything
happen to you, okay?

26:27.100 --> 26:28.324
What if you aren't home?

26:31.148 --> 26:32.828
Okay, look. Uh...

26:33.748 --> 26:36.708
the code's your birthday... 0, 5, 2, 2.

26:41.439 --> 26:43.236
And then hit... hit "arm."

26:45.390 --> 26:46.676
[Beeps]

26:47.017 --> 26:48.283
See? Easy.

26:56.020 --> 26:59.922
The code's your birthday... 0, 5, 2, 2.

27:00.024 --> 27:03.092
♪

27:33.099 --> 27:34.703
Charlie: Mayor Warren.

27:35.768 --> 27:37.603
Please, call me Claire.

27:38.249 --> 27:40.056
Damn it. Then it's "Charlie," too.

27:40.118 --> 27:40.984
[Chuckle]

27:41.207 --> 27:44.582
Thank you for making the drive up.

27:45.511 --> 27:47.945
I asked you here
to set some ground rules

27:48.047 --> 27:50.414
- before the bullets fly.
- Very sportsmanlike.

27:50.516 --> 27:52.349
We both want what's best
for this great state.

27:52.451 --> 27:56.854
So let's make this race about
education and wages and energy.

27:58.252 --> 28:00.190
You're new to the scene,

28:00.805 --> 28:02.426
but races in Maine

28:02.528 --> 28:06.330
are won on issues, Claire,
not celebrity.

28:06.432 --> 28:08.098
[Footsteps approaching]

28:08.200 --> 28:09.066
Yes, Scotty?

28:09.168 --> 28:10.701
I just need you to sign, sir.

28:12.805 --> 28:14.705
It's budget appropriations.

28:14.807 --> 28:16.827
It's a very complicated part of the job.

28:17.364 --> 28:22.079
Labor unions make it almost
impossible at the state level.

28:22.543 --> 28:25.683
You dealt with any of that
in, uh, whatsit?

28:25.785 --> 28:27.251
Red Pines.

28:28.325 --> 28:29.485
That's it.

28:29.555 --> 28:31.755
Not as much.

28:31.857 --> 28:34.158
How many freshmen
in the legislature right now?

28:34.226 --> 28:35.802
Is this lunch or a civics quiz?

28:35.904 --> 28:38.028
- You know all their names?
- Of course I do.

28:38.130 --> 28:40.856
There aren't any. Not this year.

28:41.901 --> 28:44.468
You're having a moment,
Claire. Enjoy it.

28:44.570 --> 28:46.203
But it's not what this race is about.

28:46.305 --> 28:47.168
Do you understand?

28:47.773 --> 28:48.886
There are two.

28:50.845 --> 28:51.842
Excuse me?

28:51.944 --> 28:53.510
Well, I assumed you meant
the house, as well.

28:53.612 --> 28:55.079
There are two freshmen in the house...

28:55.181 --> 28:56.513
Cumberland and Jones... both women.

28:56.615 --> 28:58.916
So, they're probably
very confused about that budget.

28:59.626 --> 29:01.869
But I look forward to setting
them straight as governor.

29:02.421 --> 29:04.821
I understand you don't want me
to talk about my son.

29:05.034 --> 29:06.990
I understand that I'm not just
a threat to you,

29:07.093 --> 29:08.625
I'm a nightmare because I am the voice

29:08.728 --> 29:10.258
of every parent's worst fear,

29:10.283 --> 29:13.230
and I actually intend
to do something about it.

29:13.332 --> 29:14.859
But don't you worry, Charlie.

29:14.961 --> 29:17.878
I don't intend to chip
adulterers, just criminals.

29:18.637 --> 29:21.638
[Lunch cart rattling]

29:21.741 --> 29:22.896
Mmm.

29:22.964 --> 29:25.769
Ah, well, this looks lovely.

29:33.185 --> 29:34.852
I'm an idiot.

29:35.312 --> 29:36.880
Danny's not home.

29:37.223 --> 29:38.873
I left something up in his room.

29:39.191 --> 29:39.993
You could have called.

29:40.446 --> 29:42.159
It was my phone.

30:17.296 --> 30:19.329
This is Adam's room.

30:19.432 --> 30:22.266
That's why I couldn't find it.

30:24.560 --> 30:26.293
You don't like me very much.

30:26.395 --> 30:28.195
I don't know you very much.

30:28.297 --> 30:29.830
I know you.

30:29.932 --> 30:32.199
You were a strange little girl
back in the day.

30:32.301 --> 30:33.563
I still am.

30:34.819 --> 30:35.871
Good.

30:36.706 --> 30:38.639
That makes it interesting.

30:43.312 --> 30:44.378
It's that one.

30:45.815 --> 30:47.214
Thanks.

30:58.427 --> 30:59.960
Are these mine again?

31:00.062 --> 31:01.328
Depends.

31:01.430 --> 31:03.330
You gonna go to that psych eval
like they told you to?

31:03.466 --> 31:04.765
What's that supposed to mean?

31:04.867 --> 31:06.133
I don't know what happened
at that motel,

31:06.235 --> 31:08.502
but I know it didn't go down
the way you and your buddy said.

31:10.773 --> 31:12.306
He was gonna kill that kid.

31:12.375 --> 31:14.675
I'm not saying society isn't better off.

31:15.414 --> 31:16.677
But you just shot someone dead,

31:16.779 --> 31:18.412
and you're sitting here
eating a candy bar.

31:20.149 --> 31:22.583
I'll go see the shrink, okay?

31:22.685 --> 31:24.251
I'll, um, open up and cry

31:24.353 --> 31:26.153
and talk all about
how I was chubby as a kid.

31:26.255 --> 31:27.955
And if you don't...

31:28.057 --> 31:30.424
I'll come back and get those myself.

31:30.526 --> 31:32.326
- Let's go.
- Where?

31:32.395 --> 31:34.068
Mayor wants to call you a hero.

31:34.730 --> 31:36.597
Gabe: All right, little man.

31:36.699 --> 31:38.432
Now that we have you
and your mom safe and sound,

31:38.534 --> 31:40.634
here's the really important question...

31:40.703 --> 31:42.603
nacho or jalapeño?

31:42.705 --> 31:43.837
Just nacho.

31:43.939 --> 31:46.473
So you're old-school. I like that.

31:46.575 --> 31:48.375
Let's get you comfortable in here.

31:48.477 --> 31:49.743
What about soda?

31:49.812 --> 31:50.644
Grape.

31:50.746 --> 31:51.945
Grape?

31:52.048 --> 31:54.548
Brian, i-it's like I don't even
know you anymore.

31:54.650 --> 31:56.417
Before things get crazy,

31:56.519 --> 31:58.585
I want to thank you both personally.

31:58.688 --> 32:01.722
What a job you did on this one. Hmm!

32:01.791 --> 32:02.956
I appreciate that, ma'am,

32:03.059 --> 32:04.858
and I'll let Nina speak for herself.

32:04.960 --> 32:06.794
I've got some chips to buy.

32:06.896 --> 32:08.462
Ohh.

32:08.564 --> 32:10.230
You've gone above and beyond
for my family,

32:10.333 --> 32:11.899
and I am so grateful for that.

32:12.001 --> 32:13.033
All right.

32:13.135 --> 32:14.768
But it's gonna stop now.

32:15.422 --> 32:16.337
I'm sorry. I don't know...

32:16.439 --> 32:18.138
You sleeping with my husband.

32:19.508 --> 32:23.177
Do you think you're special,
a one-of-a-kind snowflake?

32:24.513 --> 32:26.213
You wouldn't believe how many women

32:26.315 --> 32:29.616
take their panties off
for the dad who lost his son.

32:33.255 --> 32:35.556
Claire: First of all, Lynn has asked me

32:35.658 --> 32:38.492
to thank the good people of Maine.

32:38.561 --> 32:42.162
It's because of your tips,
your initiative,

32:42.264 --> 32:45.032
your coming together
when she needed it the most

32:45.134 --> 32:47.468
that she has her son Brian back.

32:47.570 --> 32:49.303
- [Applause]
- Yes!

32:50.261 --> 32:52.473
You know, I don't know
if you all believe in miracles.

32:52.575 --> 32:53.974
You know I do.

32:54.076 --> 32:57.978
Today's miracle was created not
just by the citizens of Maine,

32:58.114 --> 33:01.682
but by its tireless
law-enforcement officers,

33:01.784 --> 33:05.352
particularly Supervisory Special
Agent Gabe Clements of the FBI

33:05.454 --> 33:07.921
and Detective Nina Meyer.

33:08.023 --> 33:09.690
On behalf of the whole city,

33:09.792 --> 33:11.925
let's thank them for being our heroes!

33:12.027 --> 33:14.495
[Applause]

33:14.597 --> 33:16.964
♪

33:32.443 --> 33:33.676
[Sighs]

33:42.153 --> 33:45.087
I-I meant to give it to you
for Christmas.

33:48.292 --> 33:49.992
Why didn't you?

33:52.330 --> 33:54.897
It didn't seem like the right time.

33:54.966 --> 33:55.943
John.

33:56.045 --> 33:57.800
There's [clears throat]...

33:57.902 --> 34:01.003
There's... something I have to tell you.

34:06.444 --> 34:09.620
Um... we need to bury our son.

34:09.793 --> 34:11.060
What?

34:11.161 --> 34:14.030
I can't wait for a body anymore.

34:14.132 --> 34:16.612
He deserves a service. He lived a life.

34:17.136 --> 34:21.737
And... we've got to live ours
however we can.

34:25.010 --> 34:26.310
Okay.

34:27.072 --> 34:28.043
Okay.

34:31.784 --> 34:33.850
[Sighs]

34:39.958 --> 34:41.992
I'll open this tomorrow.

34:45.931 --> 34:47.243
[Sighs]

35:02.581 --> 35:04.341
You cooked!

35:05.084 --> 35:08.285
Try not to sound so shocked.

35:10.823 --> 35:13.624
Join us for dinner.
You can help set the table.

35:13.692 --> 35:15.292
Cool.

35:18.161 --> 35:19.794
Googled your girlfriend.

35:19.863 --> 35:20.974
Stalker.

35:21.076 --> 35:23.531
- She's a reporter.
- She's a blogger.

35:23.633 --> 35:25.733
She came back for her phone.

35:25.835 --> 35:27.869
She was sniffing around Adam's room.

35:31.875 --> 35:34.675
If she shows up again for her panties,

35:34.811 --> 35:36.677
tell her we'll mail them.

35:38.148 --> 35:39.658
Okay.

35:39.760 --> 35:41.482
[Drawer closes]

35:45.355 --> 35:47.455
You sure you want me to toss it?

35:47.524 --> 35:49.290
Get it out of here, or I'll eat it.

35:49.392 --> 35:50.992
[Both chuckle]

35:51.094 --> 35:54.228
♪

36:27.163 --> 36:29.163
[Sighs]

36:29.265 --> 36:31.299
I didn't want you to see it.

36:35.004 --> 36:37.905
It's the wood from the walnut tree

36:38.007 --> 36:39.607
we cut down last fall.

36:39.709 --> 36:40.975
Oh.

36:41.077 --> 36:42.877
I was gonna surprise you
when I was all done.

36:42.979 --> 36:44.745
I'm an idiot. I thought...

36:44.848 --> 36:46.380
What? That I was doing something shady

36:46.483 --> 36:47.882
right under your nose?

36:47.984 --> 36:49.183
Come on.

36:49.285 --> 36:50.518
I'm smoother than that.

36:50.620 --> 36:51.652
[Chuckles]

36:51.754 --> 36:53.087
No, you're not.

36:53.156 --> 36:54.722
- [Laughs]
- No, I'm not.

36:54.824 --> 36:56.924
[Chuckles]

36:59.662 --> 37:01.696
- What were you doing in his room?
- [Gasps]

37:03.233 --> 37:04.799
What the hell, Danny?!

37:04.901 --> 37:05.967
I told you to leave it alone.

37:06.069 --> 37:08.169
Are you crazy? You can't just
break in here and...

37:08.271 --> 37:09.504
Like you did.

37:11.040 --> 37:12.139
You know who I am.

37:12.242 --> 37:13.641
What did you take from his room?

37:13.743 --> 37:15.009
You want a story not to be written,

37:15.111 --> 37:16.118
don't tell it to a reporter.

37:16.220 --> 37:17.925
Whatever you took, give it back.

37:18.027 --> 37:19.247
It's too late.

37:21.017 --> 37:22.350
You're a lying bitch.

37:22.452 --> 37:24.008
Well, you're a stupid drunk.

37:28.591 --> 37:30.024
This obviously isn't gonna end in sex,

37:30.126 --> 37:31.424
so why don't you just go?

37:37.367 --> 37:41.119
[The National's
"This Is The Last Time" plays]

37:44.374 --> 37:47.208
♪ Oh, when I lift you up ♪

37:47.310 --> 37:52.046
♪ You feel like a hundred times
yourself ♪

37:52.148 --> 37:55.483
♪ I wish everybody knew ♪

37:55.585 --> 37:57.933
♪ What's so great about you ♪

37:58.036 --> 38:02.223
♪ Oh, don't tell anyone I'm here ♪

38:02.325 --> 38:05.693
♪ I've got Tylenol and beer ♪

38:05.795 --> 38:11.699
♪ I was thinking that you'd call
somebody closer to you ♪

38:11.801 --> 38:15.970
♪ Oh, but your love is such a swamp ♪

38:16.072 --> 38:19.407
♪ You're the only thing I want ♪

38:19.475 --> 38:23.711
♪ And I said I wouldn't cry about it ♪

38:23.813 --> 38:25.880
♪ Ahhhh ♪

38:31.154 --> 38:33.321
♪ This is the last time ♪

38:33.423 --> 38:35.056
Natural energy.

38:35.158 --> 38:37.258
Plus a little joy.

38:37.860 --> 38:40.995
♪ This is the last time ♪

38:41.097 --> 38:42.930
You think he'll do it, though?

38:44.000 --> 38:45.600
What?

38:45.702 --> 38:47.568
Take another kid.

38:50.173 --> 38:51.339
They always do.

39:12.462 --> 39:15.363
♪ Jenny, I am in trouble ♪

39:15.465 --> 39:19.166
♪ Can't get these thoughts out of me ♪

39:19.268 --> 39:22.536
♪ Jenny, I'm seeing double ♪

39:22.605 --> 39:26.073
